org.zaproxy.zap.view.messagecontainer.http

Class DefaultMultipleHttpMessagesContainer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.zaproxy.zap.view.messagecontainer.AbstractMessageContainer<HttpMessage>
      • org.zaproxy.zap.view.messagecontainer.http.AbstractHttpMessageContainer
        • org.zaproxy.zap.view.messagecontainer.http.DefaultMultipleHttpMessagesContainer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HttpMessageContainer, MultipleHttpMessagesContainer, MessageContainer<HttpMessage>, MultipleMessagesContainer<HttpMessage>, SingleMessageContainer<HttpMessage>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultMultipleHistoryReferencesContainer, DefaultSelectableHttpMessagesContainer

    public class DefaultMultipleHttpMessagesContainer
extends AbstractHttpMessageContainer
implements MultipleHttpMessagesContainer
    A default implementation of a MultipleHttpMessagesContainer.

    Note: Users of this class should provide list of HttpMessages that are loaded/read as needed (for example, from database with PersistedHttpMessagesList) to avoid keeping the HttpMessages in memory or alternatively use MultipleHistoryReferencesContainer.

    Since:
    2.3.0
    See Also:
    MultipleHttpMessagesContainer, MultipleHistoryReferencesContainer, PersistedHttpMessagesList

      • getMessages

        public List<HttpMessage> getMessages()
        Description copied from interface: MultipleMessagesContainer
        Returns all the contained messages or an empty List if none.

        No assumptions should be made on the actual implementation type of the List returned by this method (for example, it might be unmodifiable or its elements lazy loaded).

        Note: Extra care should be taken when getting the messages from the list since it might return null which indicates that an error occurred while getting a message (for example, failed to read a persisted message).

        Specified by:
        getMessages in interface MultipleMessagesContainer<HttpMessage>
        Returns:
        a List with all the contained messages, never null.
